  "chapter": {
    "bookTitle": "James",
    "delineation": "Chapter",
    "number": 1,
    "summary": "If any of you lack wisdom, let him ask of God—Resist temptation—Be doers of the word—James explains how to recognize pure religion.",
    "chapterAugmentations": [],
    "verses": [
      {
        "text": "James, a servant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve tribes which are scattered abroad, greeting.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Servant.",
            "start": 9,
            "end": 16
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Israel, Twelve Tribes of.",
            "start": 85,
            "end": 94
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "My brethren, count it all joy when ye fall into divers temptations;",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "JST James 1:2 … many afflictions;",
            "start": 48,
            "end": 54
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Temptation.",
            "start": 55,
            "end": 66
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Knowing this, that the trying of your faith worketh patience.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "GR approval by trial. TG Opposition; Test.",
            "start": 23,
            "end": 29
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Patience.",
            "start": 52,
            "end": 60
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 8,
            "end": 13
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "But let patience have her perfect work, that ye may be perfect and entire, wanting nothing.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Perfection.",
            "start": 55,
            "end": 62
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 22,
            "end": 25
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "If any of you lack wisdom, let him ask of God, that giveth to all men liberally, and upbraideth not; and it shall be given him.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "D&C 42:68; JS—H 1:11.",
            "start": 0,
            "end": 2
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Guidance, Divine; Learn; Wisdom.",
            "start": 19,
            "end": 25
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Benevolence; Revelation.",
            "start": 52,
            "end": 58
          },
          {
            "footnote": "GR reproaches, censures.",
            "start": 85,
            "end": 95
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 66,
            "end": 69
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "But let him ask in faith, nothing wavering. For he that wavereth is like a wave of the sea driven with the wind and tossed.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Prayer.",
            "start": 12,
            "end": 15
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Faith.",
            "start": 19,
            "end": 24
          },
          {
            "footnote": "GR doubting, hesitating. TG Doubt.",
            "start": 34,
            "end": 42
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "For let not that man think that he shall receive any thing of the Lord.",
        "footnotes": [],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "A double minded man is unstable in all his ways.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "1 Kgs. 18:21; Ps. 12:2; Hosea 10:2. TG Integrity.",
            "start": 2,
            "end": 15
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 20,
            "end": 22
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Let the brother of low degree rejoice in that he is exalted:",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Matt. 23:12.",
            "start": 19,
            "end": 22
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "But the rich, in that he is made low: because as the flower of the grass he shall pass away.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Isa. 40:6–8.",
            "start": 67,
            "end": 72
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "For the sun is no sooner risen with a burning heat, but it withereth the grass, and the flower thereof falleth, and the grace of the fashion of it perisheth: so also shall the rich man fade away in his ways.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "GR beauty of its appearance.",
            "start": 120,
            "end": 125
          },
          {
            "footnote": "1 Tim. 6:17 (17–19).",
            "start": 176,
            "end": 180
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Blessed is the man that endureth temptation: for when he is tried, he shall receive the crown of life, which the Lord hath promised to them that love him.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "1 Pet. 3:14. TG Blessing.",
            "start": 0,
            "end": 7
          },
          {
            "footnote": "JST James 1:12 … resisteth temptation … TG Steadfastness.",
            "start": 24,
            "end": 43
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Test.",
            "start": 60,
            "end": 65
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Exaltation; Reward.",
            "start": 88,
            "end": 93
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 8,
            "end": 10
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Let no man say when he is tempted, I am tempted of God: for God cannot be tempted with evil, neither tempteth he any man:",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG God, Perfection of.",
            "start": 74,
            "end": 81
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Evil.",
            "start": 87,
            "end": 91
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "But every man is tempted, when he is drawn away of his own lust, and enticed.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Temptation.",
            "start": 17,
            "end": 24
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Chastity; Lust; Motivations; Sensuality.",
            "start": 59,
            "end": 63
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Then when lust hath conceived, it bringeth forth sin: and sin, when it is finished, bringeth forth death.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Sin.",
            "start": 49,
            "end": 52
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Do not err, my beloved brethren.",
        "footnotes": [],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and cometh down from the Father of lights, with whom is no variableness, neither shadow of turning.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Ps. 85:12.",
            "start": 6,
            "end": 10
          },
          {
            "footnote": "Moro. 7:12 (12–13).",
            "start": 11,
            "end": 15
          },
          {
            "footnote": "John 3:27; 2 Cor. 9:15. TG God, Gifts of.",
            "start": 34,
            "end": 38
          },
          {
            "footnote": "D&C 67:9.",
            "start": 58,
            "end": 64
          },
          {
            "footnote": "D&C 67:4, 9.",
            "start": 79,
            "end": 85
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG God, Perfection of.",
            "start": 113,
            "end": 125
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Of his own will begat he us with the word of truth, that we should be a kind of firstfruits of his creatures.",
        "footnotes": [],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Wherefore, my beloved brethren, let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, slow to wrath:",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Prov. 17:27.",
            "start": 72,
            "end": 77
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Patience.",
            "start": 79,
            "end": 83
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Anger.",
            "start": 87,
            "end": 92
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [
          {
            "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
            "data-pointer-type": "media",
            "data-scroll-id": "p19",
            "title": "Associated Content"
          }
        ],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "For the wrath of man worketh not the righteousness of God.",
        "footnotes": [],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Wherefore lay apart all filthiness and superfluity of naughtiness, and receive with meekness the engrafted word, which is able to save your souls.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Filthiness.",
            "start": 24,
            "end": 34
          },
          {
            "footnote": "GR overabundance of malice, trouble, evil.",
            "start": 39,
            "end": 65
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Meek.",
            "start": 84,
            "end": 92
          },
          {
            "footnote": "GR implanted, ingrafted.",
            "start": 97,
            "end": 106
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "But be ye doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving your own selves.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Commitment; Duty; Good Works; Hypocrisy.",
            "start": 10,
            "end": 15
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "For if any be a hearer of the word, and not a doer, he is like unto a man beholding his natural face in a glass:",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Luke 6:49 (47–49).",
            "start": 16,
            "end": 22
          },
          {
            "footnote": "1 Cor. 13:12.",
            "start": 106,
            "end": 111
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "For he beholdeth himself, and goeth his way, and straightway forgetteth what manner of man he was.",
        "footnotes": [],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "But whoso looketh into the perfect law of liberty, and continueth therein, he being not a forgetful hearer, but a doer of the work, this man shall be blessed in his deed.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG God, Law of.",
            "start": 35,
            "end": 38
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Liberty.",
            "start": 42,
            "end": 49
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 66,
            "end": 74
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "If any man among you seem to be religious, and bridleth not his tongue, but deceiveth his own heart, this man's religion is vain.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Gossip; Profanity.",
            "start": 64,
            "end": 70
          },
          {
            "footnote": "GR useless, deceptive, erroneous.",
            "start": 124,
            "end": 128
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 121,
            "end": 123
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Pure religion and undefiled before God and the Father is this, To visit the fatherless and widows in their affliction, and to keep himself unspotted from the world.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Charity.",
            "start": 5,
            "end": 13
          },
          {
            "footnote": "D&C 44:6. TG Benevolence; Good Works; Welfare.",
            "start": 66,
            "end": 71
          },
          {
            "footnote": "Deut. 26:13; Job 22:9; 31:21 (21–22); Ps. 10:14; 146:9 (1–10); 3 Ne. 24:5; D&C 136:8 (7–9).",
            "start": 76,
            "end": 86
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Widows.",
            "start": 91,
            "end": 97
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Affliction.",
            "start": 107,
            "end": 117
          },
          {
            "footnote": "1 Tim. 5:22; 1 Jn. 5:18; D&C 59:9. TG Chastity.",
            "start": 139,
            "end": 148
          },
          {
            "footnote": "JST James 1:27 … the vices of the world.",
            "start": 154,
            "end": 157
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Worldliness.",
            "start": 158,
            "end": 163
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 119,
            "end": 122
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}